it’s been a journey ya’ll 🥺 i’m about to cry because this moment is bittersweet . i’ve sold thousands of hats all handmade by me . no one has ever made one of my hats … only me 🥺❤️ i’ve met some amazing people , the support was always out of this world .. especially every time i did a photo shoot and didn’t know what i was doing but everyone went with it .. and vibed . but it’s about that time i move forward with my art .. this is not goodbye forever but for now . thank you to everyone that has supported me and my art . bought a hat or two or 100 and wore them proudly . i started this brand to give voices to people that wanted to represent themselves without having to say a word and it’s been nothing but a blessing . from being featured on TSR to reaching the hands of celebrities .. the growth has been tremendous and i truly love y’all but i’m going to expand my art in bigger ways soon . thank you again for all the support 🥺🥺🥺🥺🥺🥺❤️ IVE WENT AHEAD AND ADDED A MYSTERY HAT OPTION. i will be clearing up my inventory, feel free to grab a hat while you can with this option. ❤️❤️❤️

hey guys. i want to start off my saying .. thank you for all of your support and messages. within the past few weeks i was experiencing a lot of crazy and scary things happening to my body and was recently diagnosed with PCOS. i've been struggling with this for years and was never properly diagnosed. i'm reading up on it now and trying to learn more about it and what i can do that is best for my body. if anyone can give me any advice or also has PCOS.. please reach out. while this has been a drastic change in my life i'm not afraid to share it. i recently had a rupture in my body that led me to the ER and i am scheduled to have surgery soon. life is really crazy. but... I'm grateful and blessed to have GOD and loved ones by my side. i've decided to really buckle down and get healthier. so that's my current goal. i’m sharing this because i’m getting older and realizing just how important doctor visits are . while this is my situation.. i don’t think this is spoken on enough and whatever i learn about #PCOS .. i will be happy to share . this is just a reminder to take a moment to get those check ups. i love you all and thanks for rocking with me 🥺❤️
